1
00:00:03,641 --> 00:00:10,593
I can't have the windows open, the curtains open, because there's too much light and you wouldn't be able to see me, unfortunately.

2
00:00:19,486 --> 00:00:31,506
Puran pujani Dhamman pujani

3
00:00:38,185 --> 00:00:41,890
Sangham Pujyami.

4
00:00:48,119 --> 00:00:55,731
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambuddhasa.

5
00:00:56,753 --> 00:01:04,344
Namo Tassa Bhagavato Arahato Sama Sambuddhasa.

6
00:01:05,302 --> 00:01:28,644
Namo tassa bhagavato arahato samma-sambuddhassa buddhang saranam gacchami dhammang saranam gacchami sanggang saranam gacchami

7
00:01:29,400 --> 00:01:55,897
Tuthi Ampi Bodhan Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Dhamman Saranam Gacchami Tuthi Ampi Sangam Saranam Gacchami Tatthi Ampi Bodhan Saranam Gacchami

8
00:01:56,671 --> 00:02:09,802
Tattyaṁ vīdāmaṁ śāraṇaṁ gacchāmi Tattyaṁ vīsaṅgaṁ śāraṇaṁ gacchāmi

9
00:02:10,879 --> 00:02:26,896
anati-katha-veramani-sikapadan samadhi-ami adhinadana-veramani-sikapadan

10
00:02:27,097 --> 00:02:29,260
Samadhi Ami.

11
00:02:30,102 --> 00:02:33,888
Kame sumi cacera.

12
00:02:33,907 --> 00:02:37,112
Vairamani sikapadan.

13
00:02:37,133 --> 00:02:38,996
Samadhi Ami.

14
00:02:39,818 --> 00:02:42,181
Musavada.

15
00:02:42,542 --> 00:02:45,806
Vairamani sikapadan.

16
00:02:45,826 --> 00:02:47,710
Samadhi Ami.

17
00:02:49,193 --> 00:02:51,757
Suramraya.

18
00:02:51,776 --> 00:02:54,200
Majjhapamadhatana.

19
00:02:54,721 --> 00:03:14,512
Now the one thing I forgot to mention was that sometimes the line drops, unfortunately.

20
00:03:14,551 --> 00:03:18,298
It's happened very, very rarely, so I think it doesn't happen now.

21
00:03:18,337 --> 00:03:19,479
Standing posture.

22
00:03:23,223 --> 00:03:36,558
Make sure you feel balanced, steady, grounded, and then just lifting up through the top of the head, standing tall.

23
00:03:41,384 --> 00:03:46,790
I'll just spend a moment relaxing the brow, the jaw.

24
00:03:48,312 --> 00:03:52,318
If there's tension there, you can clench the jaw and relax it.

25
00:03:55,993 --> 00:03:59,298
Shoulders, you might need a good squeeze.

26
00:04:05,685 --> 00:04:09,088
Hands joined in front or by the side, whatever's comfortable.

27
00:04:14,175 --> 00:04:22,223
Just acknowledging that posture, the energy rising up through the spine, top of the head, lifting you up.

28
00:04:23,605 --> 00:04:25,107
Everything else just hanging off.

29
00:04:25,997 --> 00:04:26,598
Relax.

30
00:04:36,637 --> 00:04:38,322
Just acknowledging that posture.

31
00:04:38,382 --> 00:04:46,096
And now draw your attention to the soles of your feet.

32
00:04:46,538 --> 00:04:47,819
What can you feel down there?

33
00:04:55,427 --> 00:04:58,132
Can you isolate the sensations of pressure?

34
00:05:09,649 --> 00:05:13,334
What about sensations of temperature, coolness or warmth?

35
00:05:23,305 --> 00:05:30,355
More subtle sensations that tell you what you're standing on, sponginess of the carpet, see if you can find a word.

36
00:05:44,053 --> 00:05:50,764
Just acknowledge how these sensations are continuously changing as the body rebalances itself.

37
00:06:00,160 --> 00:06:01,923
body rebalances itself.

38
00:06:10,279 --> 00:06:14,127
And acknowledge how these sensations arise, whether you want them to or not.

39
00:06:16,411 --> 00:06:18,776
Not under our direct control.

40
00:06:30,485 --> 00:06:41,084
Taking your time now, just come up the body, see what you can feel on the surface of the body, inside the body, areas that seem to be void of feeling.

41
00:06:59,915 --> 00:07:06,709
When you get to the abdomen, can you feel the sensations caused by the breath there, the rise and fall of the abdomen?

42
00:07:16,170 --> 00:07:18,716
Any other sensations there, maybe a bit of tension?

43
00:07:28,923 --> 00:07:30,144
What about the stomach area?

44
00:07:31,206 --> 00:07:32,327
Can you feel the breath there?

45
00:07:32,367 --> 00:07:41,079
Any other sensations, tensions?

46
00:07:55,079 --> 00:07:56,622
Can you feel the breath in the chest?

47
00:07:57,182 --> 00:07:58,524
Or is that fairly relaxed?

48
00:07:58,942 --> 00:07:59,903
Or maybe tense.

49
00:08:02,406 --> 00:08:03,226
What do you find there?

50
00:08:12,995 --> 00:08:13,776
Feel the heartbeat.

51
00:08:26,047 --> 00:08:27,447
Shoulders still relax.

52
00:08:35,697 --> 00:08:36,378
The jaw.

53
00:08:44,370 --> 00:08:44,951
The brow.

54
00:08:49,940 --> 00:08:53,404
When you get to the scalp, scan it like you did the soles of your feet.

55
00:08:53,465 --> 00:08:54,567
What can you feel there?

56
00:09:09,903 --> 00:09:13,927
Now without moving the eyes, just become aware of what's outside you.

57
00:09:15,148 --> 00:09:17,171
So the shapes and colors in front of you.

58
00:09:23,697 --> 00:09:24,457
Any sounds?

59
00:09:32,846 --> 00:09:34,729
The atmosphere of the room you're in.

60
00:09:42,961 --> 00:10:00,105
And if there's somebody in the house or flat, sense their presence, even immediate neighbors or pets.

61
00:10:07,735 --> 00:10:10,099
So attention is entirely out there.

62
00:10:18,162 --> 00:10:25,408
Now at the same time, bringing the in here, the breath, the feet and so on, both the inside and the outside.

63
00:10:34,839 --> 00:10:37,081
So this is the bubble of our consciousness.

64
00:10:38,962 --> 00:10:39,943
This is our world.

65
00:10:40,004 --> 00:10:42,466
This is what we're creating moment after moment.

66
00:10:43,386 --> 00:10:44,347
Nobody else can know it.

67
00:10:45,249 --> 00:10:46,330
It's our universe.

68
00:10:47,102 --> 00:10:48,684
We're always at the center of it.

69
00:10:52,509 --> 00:10:53,691
So we may as well relax.

70
00:10:54,051 --> 00:10:57,034
Just relax into this present moment, wide awake.

71
00:11:01,659 --> 00:11:04,322
And as it were, hang in the middle.

72
00:11:05,104 --> 00:11:11,270
Just allow the attention to be drawn now to something you see, something you hear, something you feel.

73
00:11:16,820 --> 00:11:17,581
Don't choose.

74
00:11:43,422 --> 00:11:46,725
Relaxing, abiding in the present moment

75
00:11:47,160 --> 00:12:11,177
wide awake in this mode just being we can let go of ideas of achieving something so in that mode we're always doing something now for some future result but in this mode there is no result this is the result there's no reason for being it just is

76
00:12:49,597 --> 00:12:50,359
Relaxing.

77
00:12:51,721 --> 00:12:57,130
Dwelling in the present moment, wide awake.

78
00:12:57,150 --> 00:12:59,936
In this mode, just being, there's no future.

79
00:13:01,658 --> 00:13:02,681
So there's no need to plan.

80
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:03,842
You can drop all that.

81
00:13:05,566 --> 00:13:07,028
We're never ever going anywhere.

82
00:13:08,030 --> 00:13:09,413
We're always arriving.

83
00:13:46,653 --> 00:13:50,996
Relaxing, inhabiting the present moment, wide awake.

84
00:13:52,658 --> 00:13:54,461
In this mode, we're being very passive.

85
00:13:54,961 --> 00:13:56,023
We're not reacting.

86
00:13:56,222 --> 00:13:57,144
We're not responding.

87
00:13:57,985 --> 00:14:02,168
We're just observing, feeling, experiencing whatever manifests.

88
00:14:02,830 --> 00:14:07,595
In which case, we don't have to present somebody, a person, a personality.

89
00:14:08,375 --> 00:14:12,879
We can, as it were, sit back in an anonymous position.

90
00:14:53,917 --> 00:15:03,208
Relaxing, abiding in the present moment, wide awake, achieving nothing, going nowhere, being nobody.

91
00:15:07,894 --> 00:15:12,461
In this mode, we're developing five of the seven factors that lead to liberation.

92
00:15:13,802 --> 00:15:22,033
The awareness, of course, and then there's that steadiness of attention and the effort needed to maintain just that.

93
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:27,812
A background sense of calmness, because we're not trying to achieve anything.

94
00:15:29,274 --> 00:15:30,875
And a quality of equanimity.

95
00:15:32,457 --> 00:15:35,019
A balanced mind, a balanced heart.

96
00:15:35,120 --> 00:15:38,844
So a mind that's not coming from a particular view or an opinion.

97
00:15:41,027 --> 00:15:41,788
Open-minded.

98
00:15:42,687 --> 00:15:47,774
A heart which is not coming from prejudice, fear, aversion, even preference.

99
00:15:48,433 --> 00:15:49,115
Open-hearted.

100
00:15:49,916 --> 00:15:51,817
Open-minded, open-hearted.

101
00:15:55,611 --> 00:16:03,486
That's the platform upon which we bring that sense of curiosity to investigate the Buddha's teachings.

102
00:16:04,408 --> 00:16:15,190
A direct experience of the Buddha's teachings by observing ourselves, feeling ourselves, experiencing ourselves intimately.

103
00:16:25,143 --> 00:16:42,621
Now, this mode is also very important in ordinary daily life, just to be able to stop like this after a phone call or a WhatsApp, after you've eaten, after you've done a piece of work, whatever, you stop and just see if there's any accumulation.

104
00:16:42,642 --> 00:16:44,484
There might be some irritation.

105
00:16:44,524 --> 00:16:46,767
There might be some overexcitement.

106
00:16:46,866 --> 00:16:50,090
On the other hand, you might be peacefully and joyful.

107
00:16:51,772 --> 00:16:54,475
So it's a case of recognizing that.

108
00:16:54,639 --> 00:16:59,166
And when it's something unwholesome, you just wait there.

109
00:16:59,667 --> 00:17:01,548
Just let it exhaust itself a little bit.

110
00:17:02,169 --> 00:17:06,255
If it's wholesome, of course, then you receive that with gratitude.

111
00:17:07,616 --> 00:17:13,144
Then there's enough space, enough stillness to see the next intention.

112
00:17:13,664 --> 00:17:19,972
If we can see these intentions, we'll have enough time to decide whether it's wholesome enough, skillful enough.

113
00:17:20,797 --> 00:17:25,703
But if it's unskillful, you just wait for that desire to exhaust itself.

114
00:17:25,723 --> 00:17:27,105
And then you're liberated from it.

115
00:17:28,186 --> 00:17:32,953
If it's wholesome, skillful, you empower it, of course.

116
00:17:32,973 --> 00:17:36,538
Just in this very simple way, we can change ourselves.

117
00:17:37,559 --> 00:17:44,609
But it takes this level of mindfulness, attentiveness, awareness.

118
00:17:53,382 --> 00:17:54,982
So our next intention is to sit.

119
00:17:55,483 --> 00:17:58,165
So try to take your time.

120
00:17:58,205 --> 00:18:02,770
So part of the Mahasi technique is to go slow.

121
00:18:03,290 --> 00:18:07,434
The more you slow down the body, the more you can see the mind.

122
00:18:07,454 --> 00:18:08,695
The mind slows down.

123
00:18:08,836 --> 00:18:12,419
You can see the process by which we create this world.

124
00:18:13,641 --> 00:18:22,848
And there's also a noting and noting small little notes, lifting, moving, placing, partly to stop the mind wandering and partly

125
00:18:23,065 --> 00:18:29,711
to really push the attention towards what we're feeling, sensing, observing.

126
00:18:30,873 --> 00:18:32,654
So see if you can find these little words.

127
00:18:32,734 --> 00:18:36,999
At first, for those for whom it might be the first time, it seems a little false.

128
00:18:37,619 --> 00:18:40,663
Well, it is, of course, but it's there as a technique.

129
00:18:41,403 --> 00:18:50,153
And very slowly, you'll find yourself quite used to doing these little notes and even around the house with something physical.

130
00:18:50,571 --> 00:18:52,077
Washing pots and stuff.

131
00:18:52,097 --> 00:18:55,913
It just stops the mind from wandering, keeps your attention to the task.

132
00:18:58,703 --> 00:19:00,108
Intending to sit.

133
00:19:35,897 --> 00:19:45,886
So now make sure that your posture, whether you're sitting on the floor, cross-legged or on a chair, on a kneeling stool, doesn't really matter.

134
00:19:46,468 --> 00:19:49,290
What really matters is the back, the spine.

135
00:19:51,653 --> 00:20:04,605
Just make sure that it has its natural curvature and that you're pushing up from the lower muscles, the muscles around the base of the spine and around the abdomen.

136
00:20:05,075 --> 00:20:08,759
When you do that, the breath of the abdomen becomes pretty clear.

137
00:20:10,423 --> 00:20:14,828
So you're pushing up from there, gently of course, up through the top of the head.

138
00:20:16,711 --> 00:20:18,653
There you are, sitting tall.

139
00:20:23,500 --> 00:20:29,309
And then as usual, just pass your attention down the body, just relaxing the brow.

140
00:20:29,349 --> 00:20:34,457
Eyes gently closed.

141
00:20:38,031 --> 00:20:38,732
Jaw.

142
00:20:42,517 --> 00:20:44,239
Lips together, teeth apart.

143
00:20:49,344 --> 00:20:52,647
Shoulders, give them a squeeze if there's tension in there.

144
00:20:59,375 --> 00:21:02,317
And hands on your lap, whatever is comfortable.

145
00:21:07,461 --> 00:21:15,631
So just acknowledging that posture, the energy of running up the spine, everything else, relax.

146
00:21:24,701 --> 00:21:32,388
Draw your attention now to where you feel the breath most in the body, the chest, the stomach, the abdomen.

147
00:21:33,887 --> 00:21:37,392
Now if you are already established at the nostrils, feel free to stay there.

148
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:46,323
So just adapt my instructions to the nostrils.

149
00:21:52,790 --> 00:22:02,442
So as the breath rises, as the body rises, the abdomen rises, just a little noting word, rising, as it falls, falling.

150
00:22:07,991 --> 00:22:09,541
and just relax on the breath.

151
00:22:10,588 --> 00:22:11,695
Just get in touch with it.

152
00:22:11,715 --> 00:22:14,694
What does it feel like?

153
00:24:28,222 --> 00:24:39,836
If the mind is wandering, as soon as you come out of the dream, really recognize and acknowledge the mood, the emotion, the attitude which is driving it.

154
00:24:40,436 --> 00:24:42,159
Let go of the story completely.

155
00:24:42,179 --> 00:24:45,221
It's not important.

156
00:24:45,241 --> 00:24:48,566
Thinking, thinking, worrying, worrying.

157
00:24:48,586 --> 00:24:53,791
And then just draw the attention back to the breath.

158
00:24:55,679 --> 00:25:00,864
Just relaxing the attention on the gentle sensations caused by the breath.

159
00:25:03,007 --> 00:25:11,996
Just allowing them to bring silence to the mind, calmness to the heart, stillness to the body.

160
00:25:17,060 --> 00:25:20,505
Rising, falling.

161
00:28:22,094 --> 00:28:47,712
if the mind is wandering as soon as we wake up really recognize and acknowledge the emotion the mood the attitude which is driving the mind driving the imagination let go of the story worrying worrying planning planning irritation irritation judging judging whatever

162
00:28:48,232 --> 00:29:17,920
and then as soon as you've acknowledged it just come back to the breath determined to stay there feeling sleepy or tired lift the spine you can open the eyes first just a little just to let the light in but you can open them wide keep the attention inward though and you can even stand up just relaxing the attention on the breath as we begin to feel

163
00:29:18,423 --> 00:29:47,484
more focus see if you can get a little closer just to catch the very beginning of the inbreath just stay with it to the very end the very beginning of the out breath stay with it to the very end now if when you do that you feel you get tense have more of the impression of sitting back within yourself and receiving the breath rising

164
00:29:49,490 --> 00:29:55,061
If the mind is very busy, you can note more quickly.

165
00:34:23,675 --> 00:34:35,726
As we become more focused, more relaxed, just choose your own time when you can open up to whatever draws the attention within that field of awareness.

166
00:34:36,829 --> 00:34:46,398
If it's a sensation coming from the body, some discomfort, some pain in the knee, for instance, if it draws your attention, we don't go looking for anything.

167
00:34:47,338 --> 00:34:51,724
If it draws your attention, go there, feel it, experience it intimately.

168
00:34:53,543 --> 00:34:57,686
It might be an emotion, a feeling, a mood within the body.

169
00:34:58,367 --> 00:35:03,994
If it draws the attention, go there, feel it, experience it intimately.

170
00:35:05,715 --> 00:35:21,492
But when the mind moves, always come off the mind, come off those stories, recognize and acknowledge what's driving it, the emotion, the mood, the attitude, and then come back into the body and see if you can feel it.

171
00:35:22,702 --> 00:35:39,514
you can't feel anything fine just go back to the breath the breath is our anchor it's our reference point when we're confused we just begin again with the breath rising falling

172
00:35:57,820 --> 00:36:02,853
And see if you can find little noting words for everything that you're experiencing.

173
00:36:05,621 --> 00:36:08,369
If something doesn't come naturally, just say feeling.

174
00:38:31,972 --> 00:38:42,826
becoming more aware of how we are relating to what we're experiencing, reacting to it.

175
00:38:42,846 --> 00:38:47,311
How when something is pleasant, we're drawn to it, want to maintain it, want to develop it.

176
00:38:48,873 --> 00:38:55,561
How when something is unpleasant, we want to push it away, get rid of it, turn our attention away from it, ignore it.

177
00:38:57,644 --> 00:39:00,208
Can we become aware of those reactions?

178
00:39:01,639 --> 00:39:08,759
This is the desire that the Buddha is pointing to when he says it's the direct psychological cause for our suffering.

179
00:39:10,583 --> 00:39:11,666
Is that true for you?

180
00:42:33,757 --> 00:42:39,485
Becoming more aware about everything we're experiencing is in process.

181
00:42:40,969 --> 00:42:43,251
Everything is arising and passing away.

182
00:42:43,311 --> 00:42:45,594
Nothing ever repeats itself.

183
00:42:46,556 --> 00:42:49,061
Each breath is similar but not the same.

184
00:42:51,443 --> 00:42:53,547
Everything is transient, impermanent.

185
00:42:57,672 --> 00:42:59,496
Is there anything reliable?

186
00:45:32,936 --> 00:45:41,543
When we're practicing Vipassana, we've discovered, keep discovering within ourselves a sort of observation post.

187
00:45:42,505 --> 00:45:53,653
We've become an inner observer, inner feeler, inner experiencer, just watching the process of this psycho-physical organism.

188
00:45:54,954 --> 00:46:02,742
Can we make it more plain to ourselves that everything we are experiencing is an object of our awareness?

189
00:46:03,581 --> 00:46:05,664
The pain in the knee is down there.

190
00:46:06,264 --> 00:46:08,726
Emotions are in the body down there.

191
00:46:09,467 --> 00:46:12,670
Images appear before me up here.

192
00:46:13,510 --> 00:46:14,911
They're always other.

193
00:46:15,612 --> 00:46:21,657
You can make that distance more clear to yourself by being aware of the distance.

194
00:46:21,677 --> 00:46:28,623
So you're aware of the distance between the Noah upstairs here in the head and the knee down there.

195
00:46:29,764 --> 00:46:33,487
Even between the Noah and the image that's in your mind.

196
00:46:35,121 --> 00:46:36,628
Everything is an object.

197
00:46:40,704 --> 00:46:44,338
Can the perceiver be the perceived?

198
00:49:13,813 --> 00:49:39,855
as the knower the feeler the experiencer on this observation post establish their looking feeling experiencing what is arising and passing away everything that is being experienced is happening of its own accord the body offers sensations and feelings whether we want it to or not

199
00:49:40,847 --> 00:49:47,217
The heart begins to emote all sorts of emotions, moods, whether we want it to or not.

200
00:49:48,057 --> 00:49:57,532
And the mind, oh mind, forever thinking, imagining, whether we want it to or not, nothing is under our direct control.

201
00:49:57,572 --> 00:50:00,695
How can it be me?

202
00:53:21,556 --> 00:53:24,400
Letting go now of all instruction.

203
00:53:25,842 --> 00:53:33,411
Have absolute confidence in this intuitive awareness that we are, allowing it to make its own insights.

204
00:53:34,233 --> 00:53:36,856
No need to think, no need to guide it.

205
00:53:37,577 --> 00:53:42,244
It now knows everything it needs to know to liberate itself from suffering.

206
00:53:42,985 --> 00:53:49,773
All we have to do is allow it to watch, to feel, to experience intimately,

207
00:53:50,226 --> 00:53:55,552
Whatever draws its attention within that field of awareness.

208
00:53:55,572 --> 00:53:56,436
Don't do anything.

209
00:53:56,476 --> 00:53:58,565
Don't change anything.

210
00:57:23,780 --> 00:57:27,264
When we come to the end of a sitting, it's good to reflect a little bit.

211
00:57:28,447 --> 00:57:34,014
One question we can ask is, how diligent was I in bringing myself back to the present moment?

212
00:57:34,155 --> 00:57:42,788
How committed was I?

213
00:57:42,847 --> 00:57:46,293
If I felt that my effort was good, I should congratulate myself.

214
00:57:47,175 --> 00:57:52,081
If I thought I could have been more diligent, then I should encourage myself.

215
00:58:00,583 --> 00:58:08,914
How did I deal with the various physical and mental states that arose just choose one of them restlessness sleepiness.

216
00:58:11,197 --> 00:58:12,458
Continual thinking.

217
00:58:14,862 --> 00:58:15,722
Big emotion.

218
00:58:17,164 --> 00:58:22,490
Just choose something that happened there, how did you deal with it, did you know what to do.

219
00:58:37,202 --> 00:58:40,947
If you thought you were skillful, then again, congratulate yourself.

220
00:58:40,967 --> 00:58:44,411
If you thought you could have been more skillful, well, encourage yourself.

221
00:58:44,492 --> 00:58:48,737
